project.notes: Changed to scale to cell size upon green flag -- Changed how bunnies are calculated. Changed how foxes go after bunnies. Changed all This is on to sharing with.

scripts.comment: Goal: Make your program ask the user what the weather is and take the input (1, 2, or 3) and set the weather and costume of the weather accordingly. Your logic for the sun from the handout on Day 1 should help with this script. The set block and switch to costume block will be important to finish this script.

block.l: What is the weather today? 1=cloudy, 2=overcast, and 3=sunny

scripts.comment: Goal: Make your program start plants throughout the green part of the grid. When plants gain enough energy, it will grow, and evertually, reproduce. If the plant is being eaten, it will become a seed again. Plants cannot grow too close to other plants.

Goal: Make your program start bunnies that move throughout your land, eatting flowers, spending energy as they move, and gaining energy as they eat. After bunnies acquire enough energy, they reproduce and have baby bunnies. Use the blocks below to construct your Bunny and CloneBunny scripts!
